    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Machines used in paring or thinning leather or skins. These involve feeding the material through rollers toward a knife edge, and were first operated mechanically via a crank, though now they are often automated.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
